qas.question: Where is the Arab League headquarters?
Who is the leader of Arab League?
What 2 Gulf monarchies have pledged billions of dollars to help Egypt overcome recent economic difficulties?

answers.text: United Arab Emirates and Saudi Arabia

context: The permanent headquarters of the Arab League are located in <a0_0>Cairo<a0_0/> and the body's secretary general has traditionally been Egyptian. This position is currently held by former foreign minister <a1_0>Nabil el-Araby<a1_0/>. The Arab League briefly moved from Egypt to Tunis in 1978 to protest the Egypt-Israel Peace Treaty, but it later returned to Cairo in 1989. Gulf monarchies, including the <a2_0>United Arab Emirates and Saudi Arabia<a2_0/>, have pledged billions of dollars to help Egypt overcome its economic difficulties since the July 2013 coup.
